                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13220759" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 2 Mar 2012 08:06:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch to skip the repair when there is no CFs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13221067" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 2 Mar 2012 17:20:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;don&apos;t we use length == 0 CFs in forceTableRepair to mean &quot;load a list of all of them?&quot;  iow i think the check needs to be on the result of getValidColumnFamilies.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13221084" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 2 Mar 2012 17:43:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We assert this can&apos;t happen:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;java.lang.AssertionError: Repairing no column families seems pointless, doesn&apos;t it
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I&apos;m not sure how we get into this situation, but apparently we can.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13221100" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 2 Mar 2012 17:59:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are right, I was a bit too quick. v2 attached that do that after the call to getValidColumnFamilies.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13221137" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 2 Mar 2012 18:39:01 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;We assert this can&apos;t happen&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s a good point &amp;#8211; how is this getting by the RepairSession constructor?  Do we have two bugs?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13221561" author="slebresne" created="Sat, 3 Mar 2012 11:46:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Bill do you run with assertion disabled?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13221615" author="wdhathaway" created="Sat, 3 Mar 2012 15:44:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Sylvain - Correct, we are not enabling assertions (no -ea flag).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13221628" author="jbellis" created="Sat, 3 Mar 2012 16:29:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on v2, then&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13221837" author="slebresne" created="Sun, 4 Mar 2012 10:17:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
